TRIP

PURPOSE
Check numeric telemetry in CI.

Programs emit key=value lines. trip checks them against rules, emits plain text
events, and exits nonzero when an error rule trips.

USAGE
cc -std=c99 -Wall -Wextra -O2 trip.c -o trip
./some_test_or_benchmark | ./trip -r .trip/rules.trip

RULES
Format:

key op number level event_id

Examples:

frame.ms              > 16.6    warn   frame.slow
queue.depth           > 1000    error  queue.backpressure
tokens.per_second     < 50      error  inference.too_slow
heartbeat             stale 5s  error  heartbeat.missing
temperature           > 80      warn   temperature.high cooldown 10s

Operators:

> >= < <= == != stale

Levels:

info warn error

INPUT
Accepted forms:

frame.ms=18.7
queue.depth 1402

OUTPUT
Tab-separated events on stdout:

warn	frame.slow	frame.ms	>	16.600000000000001	18.699999999999999

Exit status:

0  no failing rule
1  failing warn/error rule, depending on --fail-on
2  invalid input, rule, or argument

BUILD
make
make test

EMBEDDING
Compile with -DTRIP_NO_MAIN and include trip.h from a C or C++ test harness.

